<item>
            <title>[JCR-1530] MsPowerPointTextExtractor does not extract from PPTs with &#8364; sign</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1530</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The MsPowerPointTextExtractor class has a problem when reading PPTs when an &#8364; sign is contained. All text following that sign is ignored. Perhaps the POI PowerPointExtractor should be used instead of parsing the data by hand. As a side effect, this would simply the code. Extracting could be done as follows:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
	public Reader extractText(InputStream stream, String type, String encoding) throws IOException {&lt;br/&gt;
		try {&lt;br/&gt;
			PowerPointExtractor extractor = new PowerPointExtractor(stream);&lt;br/&gt;
			return new StringReader(extractor.getText(true,true));&lt;br/&gt;
		} catch (RuntimeException e) {&lt;br/&gt;
			logger.warn(&amp;quot;Failed to extract PowerPoint text content&amp;quot;, e);&lt;br/&gt;
			return new StringReader(&amp;quot;&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
		} finally {&lt;br/&gt;
			try { stream.close(); } catch (IOException ignored) {}&lt;br/&gt;
		}&lt;br/&gt;
	}&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
